body.name: SEDETA 63" L Shaped Desk, Convertible 86.6" Home Office Desk or Corner Desk, Office Computer Desk with Drawer, Power Strip, Storage Cabinet, Bookshelf & Monitor Stand, Retro Grey
features: 【What can you get?】L shaped desk or long computer desk is available, and various options - power strip, drawer, cabinet, bookshelf, storage bag, and a removable monitor stand. The tabletop(63"L*19.7" W) could hold two desktop computers and one notebook computer, which can help you organize your workspace more efficiently.

【Convertible Design】The computer desk has 2 kinds of assembly ways, you can change the l-shaped into a long double desk as you need. The 86.6-inch - length size allows 2 person to work side by side without compromising on space. The office desk is perfect for your friends, workmate, and you to study, play games and work together. Equipped with 2 AC outlets and 2 PowerIQ-enabled USB charging ports to provide power for up to 4 devices simultaneously.

【Multiple storage】 Where should things be kept when you are studying or working? A corner desk with drawer, cabinet, removable monitor stand, bookshelf, and storage bag can help you quickly and efficiently classify storage. The under-desk bookshelf offers ample storage space for books, files and other supplies, which reduces the clutter on the desktop and adds enough space for storage and organization under the home office desk.

【Stable Structure】 Metal frames can hold up to 550 lbs. Adjustable desk leg pads made the desk keep stable even on carpet. P2-degree engineered wood with high resistance to scratch & friction. The X-shaped structure on the side of the l shape desk helps the table to be more stable.

【Steady Construction & After-sales Service】To make assembling this sturdy home office desk as effortless as possible, we have included clear and detailed instructions, and numbered parts. If your item arrives damaged, scratched, or missing part, please feel free to contact us, and we will send you a free replacement or offer a partial refund.

reviews.reviewText: Nothing but good things to say about this desk. It’s simple and great for a small workspace. Easy to assemble and I love that the orientation can be changed. Drawer and cabinet open and close smoothly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Functional and attractive desk
reviews.reviewText: I needed a larger desk for my home office that offered desktop for writing in addition to my standing desktop frame. this works perfectly and is very sturdy. It was also easier to assemble than i had feared, although i do recommend paying extra attention to the first portion's frame assembly, as i had one side in the wrong direction and had to fix it at the end. Good value for the money!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Well maybe…but ok.
reviews.reviewText: Let’s just cut to the chase.It’s sturdy enough, but look cheap.I’m using in a shed office in my back yard so it will not get a lot of public viewing time. So it’s acceptable. It did come with a broken door. Nothing a little wood glue and a couple Dowels couldn’t fix. For the price I would have preferred to not to have to fix anything. One good thing is they gave more than enough hardware. When you left over hardware it makes you wonder, but after double checking everything is securely in place.Instruction are not good. They leave a lot of room for error. I have learned to always lay out a product before assembling. That saves a ton of time and headache. And believe me it did in this case. Yes the instructions are that bad. Might be easier to just look at the picture and assemble. It assembled quickly.Don’t sit on the desk part.Here’s some pros and cons.Pros: 1. Looks just ok. 2. Sturdy 3. Functional for a small office. 4. Plenty of hardware and backup pieces.5. Assembly time is quick, took me 30 minutes.Cons: 1. For the price? Not so happy. 2. Broken pieces. Several reviews had the same problem. 3. Instructions are terrible. But not rocket science. 4. Though it’s sturdy given the attachment point being plentiful the materials are cheap so let’s go back to, Don’t sit on it.Would I recommend this to others? Both yes and no. If it’s a front office purchase, that’s a big NO. If it’s for private occasional use, it’s a Yes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful Desk but awful assembly
reviews.reviewText: While this is a great quality desk for the cost, with lots of legroom and a comfortable height… The manufacturer needs to take a look at the assembly instructions and make some improvements. While putting together furniture is rarely an easy process, this took me over 2 hours. Part of the issue was that the instructions (mostly small pictures) offer little guidance on how best to go about the assembly (like when to turn pieces over or on their side, ensure things are oriented the right way, etc). I ended up making a error at the beginning of the process that I didn’t realize until the very end of the process, so I would have to dismantle a sizable portion because one hole was on the wrong side. The other issue was simply that I should have used an electric drill rather than using the tools provided. My hands were aching by the end. I would recommend this desk but I would rather walk barefoot across a floor covered in legos than deal with the assembly again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality for the price
reviews.reviewText: I've purchased so much assemble it yourself furniture in my life (rooms and rooms full) and most of it is pretty shoddy. This one is surprisingly substantial and good quality. All the screw holes are properly threaded, and the screw in pegs have the proper plastic threaded fittings so you're not just going into bare particle board. All parts are labeled and the instructions were very good, even including extra tips where it might be easy to make a mistake. I'm happy to report that I only made one minor error while assembling this and it was very easy to realize and correct on my next step. Fair warning, it is a ton of pieces and even as a very experienced home furniture assembler it took me several hours, but the going was easy and there was nothing frustrating about the process at all. One other big positive is how it was packaged: hard plastic corner protectors on the desktop pieces. I really appreciated that because I've had more than a few pieces of furniture arrive already damaged out of the box. Everything here was pristine. I got mine on a black Friday sale, but I think it's worth the original list price of just under $200 and I would have been happy with it at that price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice rustic L-shaped desk.
reviews.reviewText: Great desk, surprisingly heavy and solid. I love the driftwood-like color of the veneer and the crossbar accents on the door. Very stylish. It pairs well with an extra dining chair I have in gray rattan. We were going for a modern rustic beach house or coastal vibe. One word of advice, however. Definitely follow the instructions to not tighten all the screws until the pieces are fitted. It can be hard to get the hardware to line up with the holes if you don't. The most challenging part for us was assembling the drawer and cabinet side of the desk for that reason. But overall a very nice desk with lots of workspace.
